      public List<JPK.Faktura> getFaktura()
      Gets the value of the faktura property.

      This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the Jakarta XML Binding object. This is why there is not a set method for the faktura property.

          getFaktura().add(newItem);
